p.font: There are two ways to get the access token (represented by step 9):

Option 1: Via /callback response
The token is returned directly when handling the OAuth callback.
⚠️ This requires you to manage the session state yourself.

Option 2: Via /sessions/:stateid (Recommended)
The module has built-in state management. You can poll this endpoint using the state from step 3 until you get a 200 OK in a while loop (make sure to use a sleep function).
✅ This is the simplest and most reliable method — no need to handle state yourself.
